	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks @mkwong98 <br />You got it right. This is the basic idea of z layer processing. Concerning your suggestion: <br /><br />- Overlapping area detection in detail is a costly processing. For the time being i just check two shape overlap each other or not. And things sometime are quite complicated. For example in Castlevania, the bat moves in sin wave and goes completely through the ground for a sort period of time but we can not put the ground in the far layer. <br />- About the opacity and visibility, i will recheck it all. <br />- About chr ram game, do you see problem or guess it? Because i already define tile identity by it own pixel data.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


