	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />CHR RAM games can construct tile data at runtime. I'd like to see what it does with <em>Qix</em> (vectors), <em>Elite</em> (vectors), <em>Videomation</em> (vectors), <em>Hatris</em> (vertically tile-unaligned bitmaps), and the text in <a href="https://pineight.com/nes/#rhde" class="postlink"><em>RHDE</em></a> and <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=135483#p135483" class="postlink">robotfindskitten</a> (horizontally tile-unaligned bitmaps).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


